  "name": "RPlog_Battle_of_Bothawui_II_25_ABY",
  "title": "Battle of Bothawui II (25 ABY)",
  "summary": "Long-awaited New Republic reinforcements arrive at Bothawui, the Mon Calamari cruiser Deliverance under Captain Cen ('Rasi') joining the battered Rapier and ordering the crippled Saber to withdraw while consolidating the fleet's gains around the captured spaceport. Almost at once, three Star Destroyer-sized Imperial vessels under Vice Admiral Solomon Fields jump in, and the two fleets form battle lines. Fields refuses to commit the Remorseless and advances methodically, opening a grinding capital exchange while squadrons of TIEs and X-wings clash between the lines. Rasi orders the Lancer anti-fighter frigates targeted to free his fighters, then deliberately breaks the Deliverance away to lure Fields's flagship Desolator into a stern chase, exposing it to the rest of the Republic force. The gamble whittles the Desolator's shields, but the pursuit batters the Deliverance and crushes the Rapier, whose gun decks are wrecked in a chain reaction. Fields ultimately breaks off, conceding the round to the Republic, while a seething Argon -- his ship spent -- is ordered to report his status and jump out of the fight.",
